io.foundationdriven.foundation.api.module

Annotation Type Module


  • @Target(value=TYPE)
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
public @interface Module
    The Module annotation is used to indicate the main class of a module, the name of the module, the version of the module, the minimum required version of Foundation for the module, and the maximum version of Foundation.
    Since:
    2014-12-01

    • Required Element Summary

      Required Elements 
      Modifier and Type Required Element and Description
      java.lang.String maxFoundationVersion
      The maximum version of Foundation.
      java.lang.String minFoundationVersion
      The minimum version of Foundation that is required to load and use the module.
      java.lang.String name
      A name for the module to be used globally.
      java.lang.String version
      A version for the module to be used globally.
